/*
========================================================
ADDITIONAL POINTS – ACTIVITY RESULT EXAMPLE
(BASED ON YOUR CODE)
========================================================

--------------------------------------------------------
WHY RESULT IS SENT USING INTENT ?
--------------------------------------------------------
• Intent is the standard carrier of data between components
• Result data is packed inside Intent as Extras
• Keeps consistency with normal Intent communication
• Allows passing multiple values easily

Example:
resultIntent.putExtra("result_key", value)

--------------------------------------------------------
WHY RESULT KEY SHOULD BE CONSTANT ?
--------------------------------------------------------
• Avoids typo-related bugs
• Improves readability and maintenance
• Best practice for large projects

Example:
const val RESULT_KEY = "result_key"

--------------------------------------------------------
WHY RESULT_OK IS USED ?
--------------------------------------------------------
• Indicates successful operation
• Helps caller decide what to do
• Alternative values:
  - RESULT_CANCELED
  - Custom result codes

--------------------------------------------------------
WHAT IF USER PRESSES BACK BUTTON ?
--------------------------------------------------------
• System automatically calls finish()
• RESULT_CANCELED is returned by default
• No data is sent unless setResult() was called

--------------------------------------------------------
HOW MAIN ACTIVITY RECEIVES RESULT ?
--------------------------------------------------------
• Through Activity Result Launcher callback
• Callback is triggered only after finish()
• Result is delivered in result.data Intent

--------------------------------------------------------
WHY REGISTER LAUNCHER OUTSIDE onCreate() ?
--------------------------------------------------------
• Required by Activity Result API
• Ensures lifecycle awareness
• Prevents memory leaks
• Avoids re-registration on rotation

--------------------------------------------------------
WHAT HAPPENS ON CONFIGURATION CHANGE ?
--------------------------------------------------------
• Launcher survives configuration change
• Result callback remains active
• Safer than deprecated onActivityResult()

--------------------------------------------------------
WHY NOT USE startActivityForResult() ?
--------------------------------------------------------
• Deprecated
• Not lifecycle-aware
• Hard to manage request codes
• Activity Result API is safer and cleaner

--------------------------------------------------------
WHY THIS APPROACH IS BEST PRACTICE ?
--------------------------------------------------------
• Official Android recommendation
• Cleaner code structure
• Better lifecycle handling
• Works well with fragments

--------------------------------------------------------
COMMON MISTAKES TO AVOID
--------------------------------------------------------
• Forgetting finish()
• Using wrong onCreate() signature
• Not checking RESULT_OK
• Using hardcoded keys everywhere
• Registering launcher inside onCreate()

--------------------------------------------------------
REAL-WORLD USE CASES
--------------------------------------------------------
• Login screen returning user info
• Form submission result
• Image picker returning URI
• Selecting item from list
• Payment success/failure

--------------------------------------------------------
ONE-LINE TAKEAWAY
--------------------------------------------------------
Activity Result API + finish() ensures
safe, clean, and lifecycle-aware
communication between activities.
========================================================
*/
